ISIS fighters destroyed ancient ruins of Iraqi Assyrian city of Nimrud dating back to the 13th century B.C.The attack, near Mosul, took place last month, but a seven-minute video of destruction has now emerged . 
 It shows militants hacking and drilling away at 3,000-year-old relics and blowing up the ancient ruins . 
 The U.N. Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon has called the destruction of the Nimrud ruins 'a war crime'